rComments: She is a competent in her field, Polish Studies. However, I have noticed a tendency on her part to complicate matters for "polish beginners". Her first level courses have the structure of fourth level courses. Maybe this is an East European thing, an experience meant to toughen you up. Nevertheless, if you are watching your GPA beware.
She is a very intelligent professor.  Her lectures are usually interesting - she does encourage discussion among the students.  She is fair in terms of grading.
She is a very helpful and knowledgeable person.
Very enthousiastic and knowledgable about subject matter. She is not only an excellent Prof. but also a really nice person.
